00:17.392 --> 00:20.145
Are your parents terrorists?
Because, baby, you're the bomb.

00:20.312 --> 00:23.023
Jim, Jim.
Ask if it hurt when she fell.

00:23.231 --> 00:24.983
- Excuse me?
- When you fell from heaven.

00:25.150 --> 00:28.820
Did it hurt? Because I know
an angel when I see one.

00:31.031 --> 00:33.241
I'm no angel. I'm a witch.

00:33.867 --> 00:37.287
But don't tell my sisters I told you.

00:38.371 --> 00:40.999
Oh, I'm so glad
you guys are still here.

00:41.666 --> 00:43.293
What are you staring at?

00:43.460 --> 00:46.588
They have been going at it
for almost an hour.

00:46.796 --> 00:48.381
Hello.

00:51.843 --> 00:53.345
I can't even look.

00:53.553 --> 00:54.888
I know. I hate being single.

00:55.180 --> 00:56.639
Waitress coming through.

00:57.390 --> 00:59.225
Special delivery.

00:59.851 --> 01:01.561
- Hey, Skye.
- Hey, Skye.

01:01.770 --> 01:03.146
Hi.

01:05.565 --> 01:07.817
I think there's been some mistake.
I didn't order this.

01:08.109 --> 01:10.195
I know. You have a secret admirer.

01:10.361 --> 01:12.071
He ordered it for you.

01:15.950 --> 01:17.577
- Who is that?
- I have no idea.

01:17.744 --> 01:20.079
I'm just following
the bartender's orders.

01:20.246 --> 01:24.083
And apparently,
he's been eyeing Prue all night.

01:25.209 --> 01:27.712
Skye, can you do me a favour?

01:27.879 --> 01:31.049
Tell him thank you and I'm flattered,
but I'm kind of seeing someone else.

01:31.215 --> 01:33.134
- Sure.
- Thanks.

01:33.926 --> 01:35.845
This is a nice change of attitude.

01:36.054 --> 01:39.557
I'll say. Does this mean you're thinking
of getting serious with Andy?

01:39.724 --> 01:41.726
Lately, I've been thinking
about a lot of things.

01:46.731 --> 01:49.108
- She didn't want the drink?
- I'm sorry, no.

01:49.275 --> 01:51.360
She's flattered,
she's just seeing someone else.

01:51.569 --> 01:53.988
Yeah, sure she is.

01:54.155 --> 01:59.160
How about you? Maybe you'd like
to have a drink with me sometime?

01:59.368 --> 02:02.330
Oh, well, that's really sweet of you,

02:02.538 --> 02:06.125
but I'm not allowed
to date the customers.

02:07.668 --> 02:09.836
- Skye.
- An order's up,

02:10.003 --> 02:12.298
so I've gotta run.

02:47.374 --> 02:49.418
Hello, Skye.

02:49.585 --> 02:51.295
What the...?

02:53.046 --> 02:56.925
You're in my world now, Skye.

03:03.432 --> 03:05.267
You look beautiful in that dress.

03:06.310 --> 03:07.811
I knew you would.

03:09.021 --> 03:11.023
I don't understand.

03:11.189 --> 03:14.735
It's your dream,
but it's my fantasy.

03:14.943 --> 03:16.820
Where am I?

03:18.864 --> 03:22.117
You're dreaming. I'm visiting.

03:22.326 --> 03:25.579
- You're in my dream?
- Yes.

03:25.746 --> 03:28.165
But I can make it mine.

03:30.667 --> 03:32.252
You can walk.

03:32.419 --> 03:36.923
In dreams, I can do anything.

03:41.303 --> 03:44.181
I can dance in your dreams.

03:49.769 --> 03:53.189
I can alter your dreams.

04:06.327 --> 04:08.037
Hey.

04:10.957 --> 04:14.210
And I can kill you in your dreams.

04:14.836 --> 04:17.714
No, please.

04:21.801 --> 04:26.514
Did you know that if you die
in your dreams, you die in real life?

04:28.308 --> 04:30.893
- Please don't hurt me!
- Please don't hurt me!

04:32.729 --> 04:35.648
No, Skye, you rejected me.

04:35.815 --> 04:38.443
And now you gotta pay.

04:38.609 --> 04:41.404
- Please, I'll do anything!
- Please, I'll do anything!

04:43.448 --> 04:45.032
Sweet dreams.

06:30.637 --> 06:31.972
What have we got here?

06:32.139 --> 06:36.309
Her name is Skye Russell, early 20s.
She's a waitress at Quake.

06:36.476 --> 06:39.146
Every bone in her body's
been crushed.

06:39.729 --> 06:43.608
Coroner said it's as if she had
fallen off a 20-story building.

06:44.651 --> 06:47.195
But we're inside an apartment...

06:47.821 --> 06:50.115
...on the ground floor...

06:52.200 --> 06:54.160
...and her body hasn't been moved.

06:59.624 --> 07:04.921
<i>Keep going.
And press and press and press.</i>

07:05.088 --> 07:08.466
<i>Keep working it through.
And press.</i>

07:08.633 --> 07:12.929
I give up. Two weeks, and nothing's
strengthened but my temper.

07:13.096 --> 07:16.224
Piper, here's the problem.
You didn't read the fine print.

07:16.391 --> 07:19.185
See, it says right here,
$19.95 for the video

07:19.352 --> 07:21.187
and 20 grand for the plastic surgeon.

07:21.396 --> 07:22.772
Yeah, well, it's worked.

07:22.981 --> 07:26.359
She's the most desired female
in America, what every man wants.

07:26.901 --> 07:29.404
Of course men want her.
Men are no different from women.

07:29.571 --> 07:30.905
We all want what we can't have.

07:31.072 --> 07:33.575
Which is why we need to stop
thinking about what men want

07:33.741 --> 07:35.618
and start thinking about
what we want in a man.

07:35.910 --> 07:38.746
Tons of fun, lots of heat and no
strings attached. That's what I want.

07:39.998 --> 07:44.210
I know this may not sound very PC,
but I want romance.

07:44.377 --> 07:48.214
Long, slow kisses,
late-night talks, candlelight.

07:48.381 --> 07:52.176
I love love. I'd take what
Prue has in a flat second.

07:52.343 --> 07:56.222
Then you'd have to deal with the family
secret, which isn't exactly normal, is it?

08:05.231 --> 08:06.691
Did you see the coroner's report?

08:07.900 --> 08:11.237
Skye Russell died of massive
internal haemorrhaging.

08:11.404 --> 08:13.572
Her body literally imploded upon itself.

08:13.739 --> 08:15.825
Ever seen anything like it before?

08:16.409 --> 08:19.996
On jumpers, but the bodies
were usually found on sidewalks.

08:21.414 --> 08:24.959
There aren't signs of external damage
consistent with any type of fall.

08:25.626 --> 08:28.879
- In fact, there's not a scratch on her.
- Yeah, well, maybe we were wrong.

08:29.046 --> 08:31.799
- Maybe her body was moved.
- From where? How?

08:33.008 --> 08:35.719
The front door was locked and bolted,
each window had bars on it,

08:35.885 --> 08:37.888
none of which had been
tampered with in any way.

08:38.054 --> 08:41.308
Nobody but she was in
that apartment last night.

08:43.434 --> 08:45.229
It's not a suicide, Morris.

08:45.396 --> 08:49.441
And it's sure not death by natural
causes, which leaves only one thing.

08:49.608 --> 08:52.903
- Murder.
- I hate it when we say that.

09:02.204 --> 09:03.539
Here you go, Mr Manford.

09:03.705 --> 09:06.083
Chicken with rice and vegetables,
just the way you like it.

09:06.250 --> 09:09.920
Chicken well-done, light oil on
the vegetables, and rice steamed dry.

09:10.087 --> 09:11.421
Thanks.

09:11.588 --> 09:13.423
